hopobject.body: Could I order a new chequebook, please? protosterone alternative Traditionally, much of the debate around what was one of the most ambitious artistic projects of the later Middle Ages has surrounded the identity of the artist who produced them. The favoured candidate is Giotto, the genius of the Scrovegni Chapel in Padua, but that attribution is hotly disputed. Cooper and Robson wisely sidestep this whole debate, and focus instead on the work.
